How can I use HTML and JavaScript to display the title of the most streamed song in 2020 according to the official music charts of Billboard Hot 100, that has received extensive airplay on major radio stations and has garnered millions of views on popular streaming platforms such as Spotify and YouTube?
Here's an example code snippet that utilizes the Spotify Web API to retrieve the most streamed song in 2020 based on the number of streams and display its title on an HTML page:
```HTML
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
	<title>Most Streamed Song in 2020</title>
	<script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.5.1.min.js"></script>
	<script>
		$(document).ready(function(){
			var access_token = "{your access token}"; // replace with your own access token obtained from the Spotify Developer Dashboard
			$.ajax({
				url: "https://api.spotify.com/v1/playlists/37i9dQZF1DXcBWIGoYBM5M/tracks",
				headers: {
					"Authorization": "Bearer " + access_token
				},
				success: function(response){
					var mostStreamedSong = response.items[0].track.name;
					$("#song-title").html(mostStreamedSong);
				}
			});
		});
	</script>
</head>
<body>
	<h1>The Most Streamed Song in 2020:</h1>
	<h2 id="song-title"></h2>
</body>
</html>
```
Note: You will need to replace "{your access token}" with your own access token obtained from the Spotify Developer Dashboard to use this code.

